  "text": "## Access Logging Infrastructure Audit: Envoy v1.31.2\n\nThis audit examined all C++ source files under `source/extensions/access_loggers/` and `source/common/access_log/` in envoy--v1.31.2, along with corresponding `.proto` definitions in data-plane-api--84e84367.\n\n### Access Log Sink Implementations\n\n**1. File Access Logger (envoy.access_loggers.file)**\n- **Location**: source/extensions/access_loggers/file/ (config.cc, config.h) + source/extensions/access_loggers/common/file_access_log_impl.h\n- **JSON Support**: YES\n- **Details**: Supports multiple format options via oneof access_log_format: format (deprecated text format), json_format (deprecated), typed_json_format (deprecated), and log_format (recommended SubstitutionFormatString which can be JSON). The implementation in config.cc (lines 31-60) shows explicit handling for kJsonFormat and kTypedJsonFormat cases, creating JSON formatters using SubstitutionFormatStringUtils::createJsonFormatter.\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/file/v3/file.proto\n\n**2. Stream Access Loggers (envoy.access_loggers.stdout and envoy.access_loggers.stderr)**\n- **Location**: source/extensions/access_loggers/stream/ (config.cc, config.h)\n- **JSON Support**: YES\n- **Details**: Both StdoutAccessLog and StderrAccessLog use the same implementation pattern with log_format field as SubstitutionFormatString, which supports JSON formatting. The config.cc shows usage of createStreamAccessLogInstance template that handles SubstitutionFormatString configuration.\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stream/v3/stream.proto\n\n**3. Fluentd Access Logger (envoy.access_loggers.fluentd)**\n- **Location**: source/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/ (config.cc, config.h, fluentd_access_log_impl.h)\n- **JSON Support**: YES\n- **Details**: Creates JSON-formatted output for Fluentd MessagePack protocol. The implementation in config.cc (line 65-67) explicitly creates a JSON formatter: \"Formatter::SubstitutionFormatStringUtils::createJsonFormatter(proto_config.record(), true, false, false, commands)\". The record field in the proto uses google.protobuf.Struct, which is rendered as JSON with values as strings, numbers, or booleans.\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/v3/fluentd.proto\n\n**4. gRPC Access Logger - HTTP (envoy.access_loggers.http_grpc)**\n- **Location**: source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/ (http_config.cc, http_config.h, http_grpc_access_log_impl.h)\n- **JSON Support**: YES (inherently structured via protobuf)\n- **Details**: Uses protobuf message serialization with HttpGrpcAccessLogConfig and CommonGrpcAccessLogConfig. The proto as.proto shows messages for StreamAccessLogsMessage with http_logs containing structured data. Protobuf wire format is inherently structured and can be serialized to JSON.\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/v3/als.proto\n\n**5. gRPC Access Logger - TCP (envoy.access_loggers.tcp_grpc)**\n- **Location**: source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/ (tcp_config.cc, tcp_config.h, tcp_grpc_access_log_impl.h)\n- **JSON Support**: YES (inherently structured via protobuf)\n- **Details**: Similar to HTTP variant, uses TcpGrpcAccessLogConfig and CommonGrpcAccessLogConfig with protobuf message serialization. StreamAccessLogsMessage.tcp_logs contain structured protobuf data.\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/v3/als.proto (shared configuration)\n\n**6. OpenTelemetry Access Logger (envoy.access_loggers.open_telemetry)**\n- **Location**: source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/ (config.cc, config.h, access_log_impl.h)\n- **JSON Support**: YES\n- **Details**: Sends logs via OpenTelemetry protocol with attributes (KeyValueList) and body (AnyValue) that support structured JSON. The config.cc uses parseFormatters and supports custom formatters. The proto shows attributes and body fields using opentelemetry.proto.common.v1 types which support structured data.\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/v3/logs_service.proto\n\n**7. Wasm Access Logger (envoy.access_loggers.wasm)**\n- **Location**: source/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/ (config.cc, config.h, wasm_access_log_impl.h)\n- **JSON Support**: DEPENDS ON WASM MODULE\n- **Details**: Delegates all logging logic to WebAssembly modules. The format (JSON or otherwise) depends entirely on the wasm module's implementation. The proto defines WasmAccessLog which takes PluginConfig for loading the wasm module.\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/v3/wasm.proto\n\n**8. Dynamic Modules Access Logger (envoy.access_loggers.dynamic_modules)**\n- **JSON Support**: DEPENDS ON DYNAMIC MODULE\n- **Details**: Similar to wasm, delegates logging to dynamically loaded shared objects. Format depends on module implementation. The proto shows DynamicModuleAccessLog with logger_config (google.protobuf.Any) and logger_name for module identification.\n- **Proto Only**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/dynamic_modules/v3/dynamic_modules.proto (no C++ implementation in v1.31.2)\n\n**9. Stats Access Logger (envoy.access_loggers.stats)**\n- **JSON Support**: N/A - NOT A LOG SINK\n- **Details**: This is a metrics/statistics emitter, not a log sink. It emits counters and histograms based on access log data. Does not produce logs in any format.\n- **Proto Only**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stats/v3/stats.proto (no C++ implementation in v1.31.2)\n\n### Access Log Filter Implementations\n\nThese are not sinks but filters that control WHICH logs get written:\n\n**1. CEL Access Log Filter (envoy.access_loggers.extension_filters.cel)**\n- **Location**: source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/ (config.cc, config.h, cel.h)\n- **Type**: FILTER (not sink)\n- **Details**: Uses Common Expression Language to evaluate expressions for filtering access log emission. The filter evaluates expressions against stream attributes and returns boolean result.\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/v3/cel.proto\n\n**2. Process RateLimit Filter (envoy.access_loggers.extension_filters.process_ratelimit)**\n- **Type**: FILTER (not sink)\n- **Details**: Rate limits access log emission using token bucket algorithm. Protobuf-only in this version.\n- **Proto Only**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/process_ratelimit/v3/process_ratelimit.proto\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Logger | Type | JSON Support | C++ Implementation | Proto Definition |\n|--------|------|--------------|-------------------|------------------|\n| File | Sink | YES | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/file/v3/file.proto |\n| Stdout | Sink | YES | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stream/v3/stream.proto |\n| Stderr | Sink | YES | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stream/v3/stream.proto |\n| Fluentd | Sink | YES | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/v3/fluentd.proto |\n| HTTP gRPC | Sink | YES* | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/v3/als.proto |\n| TCP gRPC | Sink | YES* | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/v3/als.proto |\n| OpenTelemetry | Sink | YES | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/v3/logs_service.proto |\n| Wasm | Sink | DEPENDS | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/v3/wasm.proto |\n| Dynamic Modules | Sink | DEPENDS | NO | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/dynamic_modules/v3/dynamic_modules.proto |\n| Stats | Metrics | N/A | NO | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stats/v3/stats.proto |\n| CEL | Filter | N/A | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/v3/cel.proto |\n| Process RateLimit | Filter | N/A | NO | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/process_ratelimit/v3/process_ratelimit.proto |\n\n*gRPC loggers use protobuf messages which are inherently structured and can be serialized as JSON.\n\n### Key Findings\n\n1. **Nine structured logging implementations** support JSON format explicitly or implicitly:\n   - Seven sink implementations: File, Stream (2x), Fluentd, gRPC (2x), OpenTelemetry\n   - Two extensible implementations: Wasm and Dynamic Modules (format depends on module)\n\n2. **All text-based loggers** (File, Stream) provide explicit JSON format options through SubstitutionFormatString configuration\n\n3. **All binary protocol loggers** (Fluentd MessagePack, gRPC protobuf, OpenTelemetry) support structured data:\n   - Fluentd: JSON→MessagePack conversion\n   - gRPC: Protobuf messages (JSON-serializable)\n   - OpenTelemetry: Structured attributes and body fields\n\n4. **Filter implementations** (CEL, ProcessRateLimit) are not log formatters; they control emission\n\n5. **Common infrastructure** in source/common/access_log/ and source/extensions/access_loggers/common/ provides base classes and utilities shared across all implementations\n"
}

